<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN'S INSURANCE PENETRATION RATE IS WORLD'S HIGHEST: DGBAS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, May 11 (CNA) 05/11/07  22:24:34 (By T.C. Jiang)
</P>
<P>
Taiwan's insurance penetration rate in 2005 reached 14.1 percent,
the highest rate in the world, according to the results of a
global survey released Friday by the Directorate General of
Budget, Accounting and Statistics (DGBAS).
</P>
<P>
South Africa is in second place with 13.9 percent and the United
Kingdom follows with 12.5 percent. Japan is in sixth place, while
South Korea is in seventh place, DGBAS officials said.
</P>
<P>
The total premium income in Taiwan in 2005 was US$49 billion,
coming in at 13th place in the world, the officials said, adding
that the world's total premium income was US$3.4 trillion.
</P>
<P>
The domestic insurance market has continued to grow amid rising
demand for the protection against loss of personal safety and
assets, the officials noted.
</P>
<P>
The premium income in Taiwan has been on a rapid rise since 2001
at an average growth rate of 13 percent per year, the officials
said.
</P>
<P>
In 2006, the premium income totaled NT$1.7 trillion (US$50.9
billion), they added.
</P>
<P>
In Taiwan, the ratio of the insurance industry's total assets in
financial institutions' total assets is also increasing every
year, the officials stated. The ratio had reached 20 percent by
the end of 2006, they added.
</P>
